| {{sort|1999|907; 1999; i, ii, iii}}
| Villa Adriana or "Hadrian's Villa" is a 2nd-century complex of classical buildings constructed by [[Roman Emperor|Emperor]] [[Hadrian]] combining architectural elements of Greece, Egypt and Rome.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/907|title=Villa Adriana (Tivoli)|publisher=[[UNESCO]] |accessdate=26 June 2010}}</ref>
|-
